The paper deals with the stability and control of ad hoc electrical networks, which involves the application of nonlinear control techniques to manage the microgrid in a decentralized manner. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Control Systems (cs.SY), Robotics (cs.RO), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Emerging Technologies (cs.ET), and Power and Energy (cs.PF) sub-categories.
